The '''44th Annual Grammy Awards''' were held on February 27, 2002 at the [[Staples Center]] in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]. The main recipient was [[Alicia Keys]], winning five Grammys, including [[Best New Artist]] and [[Grammy Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]] for "[[Fallin']]". [[U2]] won four awards including [[Grammy Award for Record of the Year|Record of the Year]] and [[Grammy Award for Best Rock Album|Best Rock Album]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees/search?artist=&title=&year=2001&genre=All|title=2001 Grammy Award Winners|publisher=Grammy.com|accessdate=1 May 2011}}</ref>

==Award Winners==

